e conference]] and a phony assassination in order to kidnap a [[diplomacy|diplomat]] |- |''[[Foul Play (1978 film)|Foul Play]]'' |1978 |Comedy; an innocent librarian stumbles onto a bizarre plot to assassinate the [[Pope]] |- |''[[The Fourth Protocol (film)|The Fourth Protocol]]'' |1987 |A rogue KGB chief bent on prolonging the [[Cold War]] sends his top spy to detonate an [[nuclear weapon|atomic bomb]] at an American nuclear [[military airbase|airbase]] in [[Great Britain]] |- |''[[From Hell (film)|From Hell]]'' |2001 |A [[psychic detective]] in [[Victorian era]] [[London]] investigates the [[Jack the Ripper]] killings and uncovers a [[Freemasonry|Masonic]] plot |- |''[[The Fugitive (1993 film)|The Fugitive]]'' |1993 |An innocent [[surgeon]] is framed for his wife's murder and goes on the run to uncover the conspiracy |- |''[[Futureworld]]'' |1976 |A reporter uncovers a conspiracy to replace the world's leaders with androids |- |''[[The Game (1997 film)|The Game]]''<ref>Temenuga Trifonova. 2012. "Agency in the Cinematic Conspiracy Thriller." SubStance. Volume 41, Number 3, (Issue 129) pp. 109-126</ref> |1997 |An unsuspecting investment banker is enrolled in a mysterious "game" as a [[birthday]] [[gift|present]] and becomes the target of sinister forces, who may or may not want to ruin his life |- |''[[The Ghost Writer (film)|The Ghost Writer]]'' |2010 |A [[ghostwriter]] for the British Prime Minister investigates the mysterious death of his predecessor, which leads him to uncover the Prime Minister's secret history with the CIA |- |''[[The Godfather Part III]]'' |1990 |Rival [[Sicilian Mafia|Mafia]] factions compete to use the [[Institute for Works of Religion|Vatican Bank]] for money laundering, leading to the [[Pope John Paul I conspiracy theories|assassination]] of a reformist Pope |- |''[[Green Zone (film)|Green Zone]]'' |2010 |An [[United States Army|Army]] [[Warrant officer (United States)|Warrant Officer]] assigned to search for [[weapon of mass destruction|