'''Sorbitan monolaurate''' is a mixture of [[ester]]s formed from the fatty acid [[lauric acid]] and [[polyol]]s derived from [[sorbitol]], including [[sorbitan]] and [[isosorbide]].<ref>{{cite document | url = http://www.fao.org/ag/agn/jecfa-additives/specs/Monograph1/Additive-431.pdf | title = Sorbitan Monolaurate | publisher = [[Food and Agriculture Organization]] of the United Nations | id = FNP 52 Add 8 (2000)}}</ref> As a [[food additive]], it is designated with the [[E number]] E493.
