{{Politics of Chad}} '''Vice President of Chad''' ({{lang-fr|Vice-Président du Tchad}}) was a political position in [[Chad]] from 1975 to 1982 and from 1990 to 1991.
There were no provisions defined for succession during the regime of [[Hissène Habré]] until 1989. According to the current Constitution of Chad, the president of the [[National Assembly (Chad)|National Assembly]] is the successor of [[President of Chad]] in case of a vacancy<ref>https://www.constituteproject.org/constitution/Chad_2005.pdf?lang=en</ref>.
